//! The I13 (cohomology-preserving electromagnetic topology optimization)
//! VerificationManifest draft (bead
//! frankensim-leapfrog-2026-program-i94v.2.3.8.1).
//!
//! The independently promotable core freezes typed design fields,
//! potential-based material interpolation, terminal-relative winding-class
//! audits on fixed topology, exact-discrete coupled adjoints, event
//! detection plus fail-closed lineage invalidation, manufacturing/insulation
//! predicates, robust guarded QoIs, and independent audits of declared coil
//! routes. The maximal lattice separately attempts integral winding synthesis,
//! certified topology-change continuation, globally certified robust machine
//! design, governed industrial validation, relative differential-character
//! invariants, a constructive topology-to-route performance theorem, and a
//! separately owned maximal theorem falsifier. A weaker receipt closes only
//! its own lattice element and is never relabeled as a stronger theorem,
//! physical-validation, industrial, or population claim.

